        <h1><a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/museum-and-archive.htm"><strong>Heriot Watt University</strong></a></h1>
        <p>Heriot Watt&rsquo;s collections reflect the courses the University has taught &ndash; both now and in the past. You can find examples of art, sculpture and textiles and information on local history relating to the Currie, Juniper Green, Balerno and Colinton areas of Edinburgh. The archives and museum also have information and objects relating to the history of the University, teaching aids, equipment and instruments, and also hold the records of the long-closed Leith Nautical College.</p>
        <p>Collections can be found at both their Edinburgh and Scottish Borders campuses. The Heriot Watt museum is located at their Edinburgh campus.</p>
        <h2>Edinburgh:</h2>
        <p>The collections housed in Edinburgh cover the history of the University, history of the local area, and the art collection which focuses on the Edinburgh School graduates of Edinburgh College of Art. Selected sculptures can be seen around the campus.</p>
        <h3>Visiting:</h3>
        <p>For individual visits you don&rsquo;t need to book and entry to the museum is free.</p>
        <h3>Group, research and school visits:</h3>
        <p>Group and school visits can be arranged in advance. Email <a href="mailto:heritage@hw.ac.uk">heritage@hw.ac.uk</a> or call 0131 451 3218.</p>
        <h3>Address:</h3>
        <p>Cameron Smail Library, Heriot Watt University, Edinburgh EH14 4AS</p>
        <h3>Opening hours:</h3>
        <p>The museum is open Monday &ndash; Thursday 10am &ndash; 4pm.</p>
        <h3>Getting there:</h3>
        <p>Information on how to get to the Edinburgh campus, including directions, public transport and other routes, can be found at <a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/uk/edinburgh/maps-directions.htm">https://www.hw.ac.uk/uk/edinburgh/maps-directions.htm</a></p>
        <p>If driving to visit, it is best to use Car Park H (free parking) and walk to the library. When you reach the library entrance, turn left at the bottom of the stairs and make your way round to the back of the building where you will find the entrance to the museum.</p>
        <p>For further information visit <a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/museum/visit-the-museum.htm">https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/museum/visit-the-museum.htm</a> or see their facebook page <a href="https://www.facebook.com/hwarchive?ref=hl">https://www.facebook.com/hwarchive?ref=hl</a></p>
        <h3>Accessibility:</h3>
        <p>The museum is fully accessible to those with mobility issues. If you require further assistance, please contact <a href="mailto:heritage@hw.ac.uk">heritage@hw.ac.uk</a> or call 0131 451 3218 in advance of your visit.</p>
        <h2>Scottish Borders:</h2>
        <p>Heriot Watt&rsquo;s Scottish Borders campus in Galashiels is home to the university&rsquo;s textile and design collections. The collections include examples of tweed and tartan &ndash; some very rare, as well as furnishing fabrics, paisley shawls, costumes, international textiles and lace.</p>
        <p>To explore the collections online, visit <a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/textile-collection.htm">https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/textile-collection.htm</a></p>
        <h3>Visiting:</h3>
        <p>To visit the textile collections, you&rsquo;ll have to book. Get in touch via email <a href="mailto:heritage@hw.ac.uk">heritage@hw.ac.uk</a> or call 0131 451 3218.</p>
        <p>Group, school and research visits can be booked in the same way.</p>
        <h3>Address:</h3>
        <p>Nether Road, Galashiels, TD1 3HF</p>
        <h3>Opening hours:</h3>
        <p>The collections here are very much a research resource, so there are no standard opening hours. Please contact the campus on 0131 451 3218
            or email <a href="mailto:heritage@hw.ac.uk">heritage@hw.ac.uk</a> in advance to arrange a visit.</p>
        <h3>Getting there:</h3>
        <p>Information on how to get to the Galashiels campus, including directions, public transport and other routes, can be found at <a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/uk/borders/maps-directions.htm">https://www.hw.ac.uk/uk/borders/maps-directions.htm</a></p>
        <p>To find out more, see <a href="https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/textile-collection.htm">https://www.hw.ac.uk/services/is/heritage/textile-collection.htm</a> or visit their Facebook page <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Heriot-Watt-University-Textile-Collection-221156908005684/">https://www.facebook.com/Heriot-Watt-University-Textile-Collection-221156908005684/</a></p>
        <h3>Accessibility:</h3>
        <p>The museum is fully accessible to those with mobility issues. If you require further assistance, please contact <a href="mailto:heritage@hw.ac.uk">heritage@hw.ac.uk</a> or call 0131 451 3218 in advance of your visit.</p>
